Context: The college offers pre-programs in Business, Community Services, and Health Sciences. These programs provide smaller classrooms, built-in support from Pathway Advisors, and flexibility to explore different program streams. Students may be eligible for advanced standing or transfer credits towards future diploma programs. The college has Entry Advisors available to connect with and provides information about application deadlines, college news, events, tours, and more via sign-up. Contact information: 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college has a Social Media Hub for additional information. The contents of the website are subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
